{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Joystick view used to control various activities such as moving a character on the screen."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The View creates a Rectangular region to act as a hitbox for drag gestures. Once a drag"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is initiated the joystick appears on screen centered at the start location of the gesture. While"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"dragging, the thumb of the joystick is limited be within the "},{"code":"radius","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" of the sticks background circle."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Joystick","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"parameters":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Binding<JoyState>"},{"type":"text","text":"  you provide a binding to a Joystate  value which allows you to maintain access to all of the Joysticks state values"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"state"},{"name":"radius","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"code":"Double","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" The radius of the track","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"canLock","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A boolean value describing whether the joystick has locking behavior (","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default: true"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":")","type":"text"}]}]},{"name":"isDisabled","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"code":"Bool","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" whether the joystick allows hit testing or not (","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default: false"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":")","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"anchor":"Style","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Style"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Joystick can be themed and styled by making a custom struct conforming to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"JoystickStyle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"protocol. Conformance requires that you implement 4 methods"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"1.  "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"makeHitBox"},{"type":"text","text":" - Creates the rectangular region that responds the the users touch"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"code":"makeLockBox","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" - Creates a view such that if the drag gestures location is contained within the lockbox, the joystick goes into the locked state"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"3.  "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"makeTrack"},{"type":"text","text":" - Creates the circular track that contains the joystick thumb"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"4   "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"makeThumb"},{"type":"text","text":" - Creates the part of the joystick the moves when dragging"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"These 3 methods all provide access to the ","type":"text"},{"code":"JoystickConfiguration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" .","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Make use of the various state values to customize the Joystick to your liking.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["    struct JoystickConfiguration {","        let isDisabled: Bool \/\/ whether or not the slider is current disables","        let isActive: Bool \/\/ True if the joystick thumb is dragging or if the joystick is locked","        let isAtLimit: Bool \/\/ whether the offset of the thumb reached the radius of the circle","        let isLocked: Bool \/\/ Whether the joystick is locked or not","        let angle: Angle \/\/ The angle of the line between the pads center and the thumbs location, measured from the vector pointing in the trailing direction","        let radialOffset: Double \/\/ The current displacement of the thumb from the track's center","     }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Once your custom style has been created, implement it by calling the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"joystickStyle(_ :)"},{"text":" method on the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Joystick"},{"text":" or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a view containing the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Joystick"},{"text":" to be styled. To make it easier try using the follow example based upon the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DefaultJoystickStyle"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["     struct <#My Joystick Style#>: JoystickStyle {","         func makeHitBox(configuration: JoystickConfiguration) -> some View {","             Rectangle()","                 .fill(Color.white.opacity(0.05))","         }","         func makeLockBox(configuration: JoystickConfiguration) -> some View {","             Circle()","                 .fill(Color.black)","                 .overlay(Circle().fill(Color.yellow).scaleEffect(0.7))","                 .frame(width: 25, height: 25)","         }","         func makeTrack(configuration: JoystickConfiguration) -> some View {","             Circle()","                 .fill(Color.gray.opacity(0.4))","         }","         func makeThumb(configuration: JoystickConfiguration) -> some View {","             Circle()","                 .fill(Color.blue)","                 .frame(width: 45, height: 45)","","         }","     }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders"]]},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"struct","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Joystick"}],"roleHeading":"Structure","fragments":[{"kin